Suspected Al-Shabaab militants destroyed a newly built security camp in Mandera County in an attack on Monday night.
Borehole 11 Police Camp, built through the National Government Constituency Development Fund (NG-CDF), was reduced to ashes in the 11pm incident.
Kotulo MCA Mohamed Rashid said the attackers arrived in the township on the outskirts of Elwak town riding on motorcycles.



