Bomb experts have been deployed to Rhamu-Elwak road to find explosive devices planted by the militants.
A security report asked road users to be careful while approaching Jabibar.
“Information received indicates that Al-Shabaab might have [planted] two IEDs in Jabibar, between the area where a Kemsa lorry was burnt and where a GSU lorry was recently attacked,” the report states. The militants accuse Elwak residents of informing security agents about their activities. Safaricom mast destroyed in the 1am ambush. The Uganda Communications Commission says the channels were used to mobilise riots in November that resulted in many deaths. Residents report seeing SNA troops taking strategic positions along the border. Kenyan Uber drivers say their investments have gone down the drain.